    "body": "Seems you are working with a very small chain -- most recent fast block is `14`. The fast/snap sync modes don't work properly on such short chains, on failure, they want to roll back at least 64 blocks, probably more. I think the behaviour when restarting an incomplete sync on very short chain is a bit undefined, and not something we're going to investigate deeply. \r\n\r\nFeel free to reopen if you have more info (and a longer chain)",
